  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\nIn `Profile` -> `Sync settings` -> `Mobile data` there is a setting **Use mobile data** \r\nWhen this setting is disabled and Status is used in mobile network in chats there is an info status in chats: \"Offline, waiting for WiFi. Change\"\r\nWhich is confusing because in fact user is still possible to receive and send messages. What is disabled if offline inbox history (receiving history messages from mailservers)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\n(1) Updated translation of label in chat reflecting more accurate meaning to what **Use mobile data**  setting does and (2) maybe also concretise descriptions in Profile -> Sync settings -> Mobile data\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n<img width=\"352\" alt=\"Screenshot 2020-04-24 at 11 17 30\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/80191193-09379580-861e-11ea-8da6-85db1f998cd3.png\">\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Enable on your device both `WiFi` and `Mobile network`\r\n- Open Status and login to account \r\n- Navigate to `Profile` -> `Sync settings` -> `Mobile data` and disable **Use mobile data** if it's enabled  \r\n- Disable WiFi on your device\r\n- Open Chats main view (or any chat view)\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n- Status version: release1.3/develop\r\n- Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n\r\n",
